SUMMARY:Ruth Page’s “Center Stage at Ruth Page\,” March 20-21
DESCRIPTION:Ruth Page Center is proud to present its annual celebration of its founder and dance icon Ruth Page’s birth (1899 – 1991)\, Center Stage at Ruth Page\, Friday\, March 20 and Saturday\, March 21 at 7 p.m.\, at Ruth Page Center for the Arts Theater\, 1016 N. Dearborn St. Each night includes a complimentary wine and dessert reception in the lobby. \nEach year\, Center Stage showcases the incredible talents of the In-Residence organizations that call the Ruth Page Center home and\, once again\, features various dance companies from the Chicago Dance Community\, creating a weekend filled with extraordinary live performances. \n  \n2026 will feature another year of captivating performances from the In-Residence artists\, including: \n\nGiordano Dance Chicago \nHedwig Dances \nPorchlight Music Theatre\nPilates Practice Chicago\n\n  \nAdditionally\, the following guest artists from the Chicago community include: \n\nBoykin Dance Project\nDeeply Rooted Dance Theater\nLEVELdance\nThe Seldoms\nThe Jazz Hoofing Quartet\n\n  \n Tickets are $30 for each night or $50 for both performances. Tickets may be purchased at RuthPage.org.
URL:https://evanstonmade.org/event/ruth-pages-center-stage-at-ruth-page-march-20-21/2026-03-20/
LOCATION:Ruth Page Center for the Arts\, 1016 N. Dearborn Ave.\, Chicago\, IL\, 60610
CATEGORIES:Dance
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://evanstonmade.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/CenterStageatRuthPage_2026-scaled.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Ruth Page Center for the Arts":MAILTO:info@ruthpage.org
END:VEVENT
