SUMMARY:Noyes Cultural Arts Exhibit: The Rhythm of the Natural World
DESCRIPTION: The Rhythm of the Natural World\, a new exhibition of paintings by Alice Matthew\, will be available for viewing at the second-floor gallery of the Noyes Cultural Arts Center (927 Noyes Street\, Evanston\, Illinois) from March 27 to May 11\, 2026. Free public gallery hours are available Monday through Saturday\, 10 a.m.-6 p.m.\, and on Sundays\, 10 a.m.-5 p.m.  \n  \nThe opening reception will take place on Friday\, March 27th from 4pm to 7pm. Beverages and snacks will be offered.
URL:https://evanstonmade.org/event/noyes-cultural-arts-exhibit-the-rhythm-of-the-natural-world-2/
LOCATION:Noyes Cultural Arts Center\, 927 Noyes Street\, Second Floor Gallery\, Evanston\, IL\, 60201\, United States
CATEGORIES:Artist Reception,Community,Exhibition,Gallery Shows
